TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {26730=The late Tony Greig is a great example. He was part of the Channel Nine commentary team that has been calling cricket since about 1843, and he used to infuriate me no end. His raucous yells at the fall of a wicket, his misidentifications, his gleeful stabs at all things Australian, and his general habit of severe overexcitement all contributed to making Greig the bete noire of Aussie cricket lovers. But after his sad and untimely passing, hell, we miss him. There's an unfillable hole in the cricket without that overexcited shout.}
